<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 2:47AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Oldham and
southeastern Hartley Counties through 315 AM CDT...
At 247 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of Romero, or 21 miles east of Nara Visa, moving
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Channing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
